#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/index.rst:5
msgid "Tools Reference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/index.rst:7
msgid ""
"This section provides reference for the main tools in the :ref:`Emscripten "
"toolchain <about-emscripten-toolchain>`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/index.rst:9
msgid ""
":ref:`emccdoc` *Emcc* is used to call the Emscripten compiler from the "
"command line. It is effectively a drop-in replacement for a standard "
"compiler like *gcc* or *clang*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/index.rst:12
msgid ""
":ref:`emsdk`: *Emsdk* is used to perform all SDK maintenance. You can use it "
"to download, install, activate, and remove SDKs and tools, and even to build "
"and use the latest compiler from source on GitHub."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/tools_reference/index.rst:15
msgid ""
":ref:`emcmdprompt` This prompt is used to call *Emscripten* from the command "
"line on Windows. It is configured with the correct system paths and settings "
"to point to the active Emscripten SDK/tools."
msgstr ""
